content:
Verify Migrated Articles in the Validation Stage

After verifying articles in the Activation stage, verify them again during the Validation stage of the Lightning Knowledge Migration Tool. This stage verifies articles in Lightning Experience.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience
Salesforce Knowledge is available in Essentials and Unlimited Editions with Service Cloud.
User permissions needed:
To view articles: View All on Knowledge and Knowledge User
To use the Lightning Knowledge Migration Tool: Knowledge User and Customize Application

Finish the verification process during the Validation stage. Check that the Lightning Knowledge Migration Tool is in the Validation stage.
Locate the new knowledge article ID in the URL of an article in Salesforce Classic.
Overwrite the ID with the corresponding old ID from the previous knowledge base version.

Open the same article in Lightning Experience and review it alongside the article in Salesforce Classic.
Verify the following items:
Details Section: Title, URL name, Smart Links, custom fields
Related lists: cases, work orders, promoted search terms, files
Feeds: posts, comments, attachments, mentions, topics, likes, Following
Smart Links: directs to the new version of the linked article
URL redirects: opens the new article using the old ID

DID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?
Yes
No
title: Verifying Migrated Articles in Service Cloud
